progress locally while production account sync remains gated behind verified email delivery and privacy review.</p><p>A concept graph declares prerequisites, scored prompts are checked against a vendored FLELex vocabulary source, and deterministic tests protect the difference between finishing an activity and demonstrating learning.</p><ul class="project-proof" aria-label="French for Life evidence"><li><strong>A1</strong><span>source-backed mission</span></li><li><strong>13+</strong><span>consent-aware onboarding</span></li><li><strong>E2E</strong><span>Playwright release checks</span></li><li><strong>Safe</strong><span>account sync fails closed</span></li></ul><ul class="tag-list" aria-label="French for Life project skills"><li>Next.js</li><li>TypeScript</li><li>Supabase</li><li>Curriculum modelling</li><li>Playwright</li><li>Vitest</li><li>Privacy controls</li></ul><div class="project-card-actions"><a class="button button-primary" href="https://french-learning-platform-one.vercel.app" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Try French for Life</a><a class="button button-ghost" href="https://github.com/JamieP-205/french-learning-platform" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">View public source</a></div></div></article><article class="project-card project-card-flagship project-card-groundwork"><figure class="project-card-media"><img src="assets/groundwork-card.svg" alt="Groundwork project graphic showing a guided learning path, SQL result table and personal guidebook."></figure><div class="project-card-body"><p class="eyebrow">Private adaptive learning system</p><h3>Groundwork</h3><p>A local React app built to rebuild my first-year computing knowledge and prepare for second year. It chooses the next useful activity from recorded evidence, explains why it was selected and prevents tests or portfolio work from appearing before the required teaching.</p><p>Groundwork includes a real SQLite-powered fifteen-stage SQL path, checkpoint gating, mistake-driven remediation, a personal Guidebook derived from evidence, migrations for older progress data and continuous responsive checks from 320 to 1920 pixels.</p><ul class="project-proof" aria-label="Groundwork evidence"><li><strong>206</strong><span>runtime assertions</span></li><li><strong>45</strong><span>Chromium smoke checks</span></li><li><strong>15</strong><span>guided SQL stages</span></li><li><strong>30/49</strong><span>fully taught topics</span></li></ul><ul class="tag-list" aria-label="Groundwork project skills"><li>React</li><li>TypeScript</li><li>SQL.js</li><li>Playwright</li><li>Adaptive rules</li><li>Data migrations</li><li>Local-first design</li></ul><div class="project-card-actions"><span class="project-availability">Private local project; architecture and verification are documented in the case study.</span></div></div></article></div><div class="project-group-heading project-group-heading-secondary"><p class="eyebrow">Production and service work</p><h3>Projects built around real users, deployment constraints and clear boundaries.</h3></div><div class="project-card-grid"><article class="project-card project-card-production"><figure class="project-card-media"><img src="assets/coast-home-top.jpg" alt="Screenshot of the Coast Internet Radio homepage showing the hero section, live listening area and now playing panel."></figure><div class="project-card-body"><p class="eyebrow">Live production website</p><h3>Coast Internet Radio</h3><p>The website for a small Newry radio station